CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 13, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - 'Miss Carey' owned this double house, now falling apart, at Peach Way and Webster Ave. Bought 50 years ago, 'Miss Carey' was well known in district for many years."
TitMainTitle: Two row houses with asphalt brick siding, wooden steps, and missing windows, Webster Avenue at Peach Way, Hill District
